After updating to latest head, my code stopped building, and I nailed it down to #1142.

Before updating, the following code builds (this is not actually my code, but due to header inclusion order it ends up being somewhat similar).
```cpp
#include <windows.h>
#include <spdlog/spdlog.h>
#include <dwmapi.h>
```

after updating to latest commit, it doesn't. This is caused by uxtheme.h (included by dwmapi.h) depending on the NEAR define provided by windows.h, however spdlog undefined this macro in-between so even if dwmapi.h includes windows.h, compilation breaks.

```
